THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 232 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. To the extent that money is available, the Governor’s Office of
4 Workforce Innovation shall establish and carry out a program for the placement
5 of career coaches in middle schools and junior high schools.
6 2. The program established pursuant to subsection 1 must be designed to
7 provide pupils enrolled in middle school or junior high school with information
8 and guidance, inside or outside the classroom, for:
9 (a) The exploration of career pathways; and
10 (b) The development of knowledge, training and skills required for career
11 readiness, including, without limitation, [information and guidance regarding]
12 financial literacy, and the opportunities available for such development in high
13 school.
14 3. For the purpose of establishing and carrying out the program set forth in
15 subsection 1, the Office:
16 (a) Shall collaborate with any appropriate persons or entities, including,
17 without limitation, a state agency, school district or other local governmental
18 agency, chamber of commerce, nonprofit organization, trade association and
19 regional development authority, as defined in NRS 231.009.
20 (b) May:
21 (1) Apply for and accept any gift, donation, grant or other source of
22 money; and
23 (2) Within the limits of available money, enter into contracts with or
24 award grants to persons or entities that have the appropriate expertise to provide
25 any services or resources necessary to assist the Office in establishing or carrying
26 out the program.
27 Sec. 2. NRS 232.900 is hereby amended to read as follows:
28 232.900 As used in NRS 232.900 to 232.990, inclusive, and section 1 of this
29 act, unless the context otherwise requires:
30 1. “Department” means the Department of Employment, Training and
31 Rehabilitation.
32 2. “Director” means the Director of the Department.

